The following code fails:
```
module t (/*AUTOARG*/
    // Outputs
    out,
    // Inputs
    clk, a0
    );

    input clk;
    input logic [4:0] a0;

    output logic [4:0] out;

    always @( posedge clk) begin
       if (a0 inside {5'b1_1?1?})
          out = a0;
    end

endmodule // t

```
Giving the error:
```
%Error: t_lint_unsupported_tristate.sv:19: Unsupported tristate construct: EQWILD

```
(Line 19 is @if (a0 inside {5'b1_1?1?})@)

VCS accepts this code.
